      "span_text": "Subject selection and rearing history has been fully described in other publications (Bauman et al., 2004a,b; [CITATION_1] . Briefly, subjects were 24 juvenile rhesus macaque monkeys (average age 34 months) that had previously received bilateral ibotenic acid lesions of either the amygdala (five females, three males) or hippocampus (five females, three males), or sham control operations (four females, four males)."
    }
